header.gameNote: MOUNTAIN WEST MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: UNLV 73, Utah 61
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Freshman guard Anthony Marshall led UNLV with 13 points and a season-best 12 rebounds and the Runnin' Rebels avenged Utah's regular-season sweep with a 73-61 victory in the Mountain West Conference quarterfinals Thursday night. Tre'Von Willis also scored 13 points for the third-seeded Runnin' Rebels (24-7), who will face 14th-ranked BYU in the semifinals Friday night. The second-seeded Cougars (29-4) defeated TCU. Utah (14-17) trailed just 29-25 at halftime after consecutive 3-pointers by Luka Drca, Marshall Henderson and Chris Hines in the closing minutes. But the Utes didn't bring that momentum out of the locker room. UNLV used a 10-0 run to take a 41-30 lead in the opening minutes of the second half. The Utes swept the Runnin' Rebels during conference play, winning 73-69 in Las Vegas in January and 66-61 in Salt Lake City last month. It was Utah's first sweep of UNLV in five years.
